function sumPrefixScores(s) {
    let n = s.length;
    let sumScores = 0;
    let longestCommonPrefix = 0;
    for (let i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        if (s[i] === s[n - 1 - longestCommonPrefix]) {
            longestCommonPrefix++;
        } else {
            longestCommonPrefix = 0;
        }
        sumScores += longestCommonPrefix;
    }
    return sumScores;
}
```

    We iterate through the input string in reverse order. For each character, we check if it is equal to the corresponding character in the longest common prefix (LCP) of s[i] and s[n]. If they are equal, we increment the LCP, otherwise, we set the LCP to zero. The sum of the scores is updated by adding the current value of LCP to the running sum. Finally, the sum of all LCP scores is returned.

